-- HK-listed property stocks up on reports China may ease home ownership rules
-- 
-- Tue Apr 01, 2014 11:40PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, April 2 (Reuters) - Shares of Hong Kong-listed property companies gained on Wednesday, led by China Resources Land Ltd <1109.HK>, after state media reported that several mainland cities may relax home ownership restrictions.

China Resources Land rose as much as 4.8 percent, Sun Hung Kai Properties Ltd <0016.HK> climbed 3.8 percent and Country Garden Holdings Co Ltd <2007.HK> jumped 7 percent. The Hong Kong property sub-index climbed 2.8 percent, beating a 0.3 percent gain for the benchmark Hang Seng Index <.HSI>. The Shanghai Securities Journal reported that local governments in Hangzhou and Changsha are planning to relax restrictions on the number of houses homeowners can purchase, citing anonymous sources.